## Table of contents (in the README)

- Place the **Table of Contents (TOC)** near the top, after a short intro (1–3 sentences).
- Use **anchor links** so readers can jump to sections. In GitHub/GitLab, anchors are usually auto-generated from headings (lowercase, spaces → hyphens).

Example:

```markdown
## Table of Contents

- [Overview](#overview)
- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [API Reference](#api-reference)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
```

This gives developers a map of the README and speeds up navigation. See [GitHub’s generated IDs](https://github.com/jch/html-pipeline/blob/main/lib/html/pipeline/toc_filter.rb) for how heading anchors work.

