## Diagrams

Use **Mermaid** for flow or structure when it helps more than text. Prefer 1–2 diagrams per README (e.g. high-level architecture, or “where to start”).

**Flow: how a new developer might use the README**

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  A[Open README] --> B[Read Overview]
  B --> C[Check Requirements]
  C --> D[Install]
  D --> E[Run Example]
  E --> F[Link to API Docs]
```

**Typical README section flow**

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  subgraph README
    O[Overview]
    I[Installation]
    U[Usage]
    R[Reference]
  end
  O --> I --> U --> R
```

Keep diagrams simple. For syntax and options, see [Mermaid docs](https://mermaid.js.org/intro/).

