## External references

Link to official or canonical docs so developers can go deeper without leaving the README:

- **APIs**: Link to the official API reference or OpenAPI/Swagger URL.
- **Libraries**: Link to the library’s README or “Getting started” (e.g. [Requests](https://requests.readthedocs.io/en/latest/), [httr](https://httr.r-lib.org/)).
- **Markdown**: [CommonMark](https://commonmark.org/help/) and [GitHub Flavored Markdown](https://github.github.com/gfm/) for syntax.
- **Mermaid**: [Mermaid live editor](https://mermaid.live/) and [documentation](https://mermaid.js.org/intro/).

Example in README:

```markdown
## API usage

This client wraps the [Foo API](https://docs.foo.com/api). For full endpoint details, see the [official API reference](https://docs.foo.com/api/reference).
```

