## Quick checklist

When writing or reviewing a developer-focused README:

- [ ] Single `#` title; `##` and `###` for sections.
- [ ] TOC with anchor links near the top.
- [ ] Short overview (what it is, why it exists).
- [ ] Clear installation/run steps with copy-paste code blocks.
- [ ] At least one usage example; link to more.
- [ ] 1–2 Mermaid diagrams only if they add clarity.
- [ ] Bullets for options/features; numbers for ordered steps.
- [ ] Links to external API/library docs where relevant.
- [ ] Contributing and/or license section if the repo is open source.

